      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUICK COOKIE (5) got well back over 1200m at Port Hedland last time and never threatened, eventually finishing in seventh. Has her share of talent. Hard to beat in this suitable race. PERCUSSION PRINCE (7) showed good early dash at the first run after a spell last time out and led for most of the way before being claimed and finishing 2 lengths away in third over 1200m at Port Hedland. Well-placed and should be tough to rein in again. HOLDOUT (6) last appeared a month ago over 1720m at Narrogin when he finished ninth. This is his first run for the Timothy Pike stable. One of the genuine hopes in the race. BIG KARRI (2) has not won for a long while. Last raced on May 9 when beaten 5 lengths into sixth at Port Hedland over 1200m. Can break the run of outs.",
